==English==
===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman ''[[assoiler]]'', from the tonic stem of Old French ''[[asoldre]]'' (modern ''[[absoudre]]''), from Latin ''[[absolvere]]'' ‘absolve’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/əˈsɔɪl/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} {{archaic}} To [[absolve]], [[acquit]]; to release from blame or sin.

